INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (6709, 88903, '2013-10-03 12:04:31', '2013-10-03 04:04:31', '<div>\r\n<div>Trying to think about your daily life, including the roads you walked or drove and the places you ever participated. Could you distinguish them day from day after 2 weeks passed? The highly repeatability of routine activities, such as commuting, dining, even shopping and pedestrian habit, cause our brains ambiguous. Several geographic studies further indicated members within different social entities such as income, racial, sexual suffer distinct activity pattern. The wise and wealthy group reveals high flexibility compares to commuters who are confined to small area near their residential and working space. Accordingly, understanding consumer\'s behavior under hierarchy context could encourages distributors in banking and retail enhance their insight, for instance <i>where and when does our costumer usually appear?</i> <i>How far does costumer be willing to reach us? Are mobile/on-line services important for specific segmentation?</i> The RTZ consumer survey system developed by getchee realizes capability to collect to-and-from information from respondents. However, it is an enormous challenge that how could we analyze these activity records in space and time simultaneously.\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div>The solution comes from Scandinavia, Torsten Hägerstrand created time geography in 1969 and it is now widely employed by urban planner, resource partitioner, environmental criminologist feminist sociologist even in therapeutic assessment to cancer patients. Time geography describes individual as a space-time path within a situational aquarium: The x-y plane traditionally belongs to geographic space, and z-axis represents temporal dimension. As figure portrays, every space-time path records past movement of every people in specific duration. The space-time prism, which shows individuals\' possible behavior in space-time given their capability and coupling constraints, therefore projects individual\'s potential path area inscribed where a woman/man could reach within a day/week/month/year. A study in Beijing grouped several thousands of paths by multi-level clustering and discovered that similar demographic characteristics exist in people who are put into the same group. The commuters who deeply relied on public transit are restricted to two small area: home and work place. Furthermore, the long working hours reduce their potential area ups to one kilometer for 15~20 minutes walk. Thus, mass-oriented storefront should be considered to locate within the hinterland or nobody wish to go. In counterpart, location continence is not the crucial concern for affluence, but only attractiveness. Distributors could be benefited to review whether the alignment is conformed between their branch network and consumer behaviors by space-time intensity (do not forget the intensity could change hour to hour during a day, and day to day between weekday and weekend). It\'s time to shift our glance to a wider, more integrated perspective. getchee, under adequate GIS professions, could greatly enrich our understandings of market through modeling consumer behaviors in exciting time-geographic approach. </div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div><img alt="" src="http://www2.geog.okstate.edu/users/HongboYu/figure/stps.gif" width="585" height="261" /></div>\r\n</div>', 'Time geography: an unconventional analytic approach', 0, '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-10-14 09:22:58', '2013-10-14 01:22:58', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=6709', 0, 'post', '', 0, ''); 
